cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with learning 3D shapes from single images using generative models. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of variational auto-encoder and adversarial methods for training the generative model. 
3. cs.GR (Graphics) is relevant as the paper deals with inverse graphics, which involves the generation of 3D shapes from 2D images. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of generative models for unsupervised learning of 3D shapes. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also relevant as the paper discusses the use of neural networks for learning 3D shapes from single images.
